## 2. Dhaliwal — Winner Pyramid

**Trader:** Daljit Dhaliwal — pyramid into early winners without adding new risk.

**Files:** `winner_pyramid.py` (clientId=138), `scheduler.py → job_options_manager`

**What changed:**
- New script `winner_pyramid.py` runs every 30 min alongside options manager
- Checks every long position entered within the last 2 days
- If unrealized P&L ≥ 1R (= ATR × stop_mult / entry_price), adds 50% more shares
- Immediately moves stop to breakeven (entry_price × 0.999)
- De-duped via `logs/pyramid_log.jsonl` — never pyramids the same position twice per day
- Cap: `MAX_PYRAMID_PER_DAY = 3` to prevent runaway on volatile days

**Effect:** Converts early momentum into a risk-free runner. The add costs nothing if
the stop is now at breakeven; the worst case is exiting flat.

> **Updated 2026-03-26 (Next Gen):** A second pyramid layer (Kullamägi) now runs after Dhaliwal.
> When open profit ≥ 2× ATR, an additional add is funded from 30% of the open-profit collateral.
> See `114-next-gen-market-wizards.mdc §6` for full details.

